The paper deals with image processing and computational photography, which are closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The proposed method involves estimation and correction of illumination, which is a common problem in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also employs a multi-exposure image fusion technique, which is a popular approach in machine learning (cs.LG) for improving image quality.
